Triton Preparing Sale of Installation Company Bravida, DI Says

-- B y   K i m   M c L a u g h l i n
-- 
2011-10-14T05:55:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-14/triton-preparing-sale-of-installation-company-bravida-di-says.html
Bravida AB, the heating and plumbing
installation company, may be put up for sale by its owner,
private equity group Triton, Dagens Industri said, without
saying how it got the information.  Triton bought Bravida in 2006 from  Telenor ASA (TEL)  and other
shareholders. The company is valued at between 6 and 8 billion
kronor ($900 million - $1.2 billion), DI said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kim McLaughlin at 
 kmclaughlin6@bloomberg.net  